Dude, this is great! You know all the Stations of the Cross, right, Stan?

This is gonna be fun.
You're too fat to be Jesus!
Stan should be Jesus.
You're such a fat baby!

Aw man, at least the real Jesus didn't weigh 400 pounds!
Yeah. That looks pretty good.
Yeah, me too.
Cartman, how stupid are you?! Didn't you read the Bible? We have to leave you up there until you die, and then you come back to life in three days.
Then I can give it to my dad. [both turn and leave]
Come on. Let's go see how Cartman is doing with his uh, urection.
Now we just gotta wait for his urection, and I can give it to my dad.
How come you're not dead yet, Cartman?!
Yeah. So hurry up and die, you piece of crap! [he and Stan leave]
We know how to fart, Mr. Mackey!
Jesus Christ! [the boys cover their noses with their jackets]
Dude, I think you pooed a lot.
God, that was not cool at all, dude!

Sick!
It's too bad Cartman can't be here to enjoy this.

Well, actually, Cartman's getting a nurection. But then, we're gonna give it you. Sooo, buck up! [his parents just look at him. He grins and walks away]
She's not worried about you.
How stupid do you think we are?! Now you die on that cross and get resurrurected before I kick your ass!
Yeah, I noticed that too. Let's go get some ice-cold lemonade.
[throws a stone] Yeah, take that!
...Oh, yeah. Sorry.
Dude, those people are pissed!
Where's your dad?
Well, you have to help him, just like I have to help my dad.
Dude, that was Star Trek again.
"The needs of the many outweigh the needs of the few?" That was Wrath of Khan.
She's upstairs.
Really? Great! I don't have to worry about that anymore. [Ike hops onto the armchair next to Kyle]
Well, my dad is, too.
I forgot all about him. [they leave]
Wow!
Dude! You're still alive, Cartman?
I wonder how come Cartman's not in school today?
Yeah. [sees Cartman] Oh, here he comes.
Why?
Dude, just ask Chef for help. He always knows what to do.
Mr. Derp?
Dude! I hate Mr. Derp!
[looks back] Shut up, Cartman!
Yeah, but we didn't believe them.
Moving in?!
But Chef always helps us with our problems. When we have a problem, Chef sings to us and makes it better.
This... is insane. [ "Oh, can't you see the-"  ]
That bitch!
He didn't even seem like Chef. He seemed like a empty shell of a man.

Look, we've just gotta get Chef alone. He won't listen to reason with that hooker around.
Good idea.
They said that Chef works in one of these buildings [the boys run into Cartman in front of Steinburg & Burgstein Accounting.]
Dude! Just take them off!
He's a big guy, with a beard.
We need you, Chef.
Chef, this place isn't you!
No way, dude!
Chef should be here any minute.
[pissed] I can't believe it!
All right, mister! You better have a good explanation for why you didn't show up to play ball!
Well, we've got something to tell you about Veronica, Chef!
Mr. Garrison, can we talk to you?
All right. Mr. Garrison, have you ever had a friend who got a new girlfriend, and then stopped being your friend, and it pissed you off?
That's it!
This is totally what's happening!
Thanks, Mr. Garrison.
Come on guys! We gotta go tell Chef he's in love with a succubus.
Oh, hi. Is Chef here? We have to talk to him.
There he is! [rushes in]
We have to talk to him!
What's tree-fitty?

Well, you are taking Chef from us. [Kenny has loosened his hood]
[pointing to Veronica] This is not a woman! It is a succubus!
[unmoved] Oh, you can pretend all you want! You're not fooling anybody!
I guess there's nothing we can do. Chef likes her more than us.
Here! Here! Look at this. It says "The succubus enchants its victim with an eerie melody. This is the Succubi power. Only playing this melody backwards can vanquish the succubus power."
I don't know.
Hey yeah! What's that song she always sings?  There's got to be a morning after.
[doubting] In three hours.
Ah man! I can't keep my eyes open. [Cartman is nodding off, too]

[joins in] Bitch.
Dirty bitch.

Cartman!! Wake up you fat piece of crap!! [Kenny punches Cartman]
You bastard!
It's great to have you back Chef!
This is sweet, being rugged outdoorsmen. ["Hey you guys, sing the song!"] Facing the wilderness, not having to be home until 8:30,... [Cartman gets up and walks away]
Just go behind a tree.
Cartman, don't be such a baby! We're supposed to be rugged outdoorsmen!
You just squat, stupid! [Cartman begins to lower his pants...]
Watch out for ground eels! [he, Stan and Kenny begin to laugh]
What do you have to think about?
No way, dude!
What?
[steps in the poo and looks at his shoe] Aw, Cartman! You're supposed to bury it!
Over here!
It just ran by here a second ago. [rustling is heard]
[annoyed] It's stupid.
You don't like anything, Cartman! [the creature is shaking from fright, and Cartman looks at it affectionately]
Did you smoke some of your mom's crack?

[softly, curtly] Dude, have you ever heard of whispering?!
What are you doing, fatass?!
They want you to have sex, God-damnit!!
Shut up!!
Dude, I don't wanna watch this thing have a baby.
Maybe their baby will be still-born, like Cartman was. [he and Stan laugh]
Gross!
Dude, this sucks ass!
We just have to show you this new species because you're the Department of Interior guy now. Soon, they'll all be eaten by bears.
[pointing] There it is! [a shot of Kenny wearing twigs] That must be of the antelope family.
Cartman! Wait!
Dude! I've never seen Cartman care so much about something.
Mr. Adler?
Yeah, you are! You always get in trouble.
[hushed, to Stan] Dude, shop class sucks. Maybe we should have taken home ec.

And then Craig was all like, "Tweek is scared o'me. He's a big chicken." And he started doing an impersonation of you being a chicken; [Stan watches as Kyle demonstrates] well, everybody in the world saw it!
Well, everyone in the world thinks you are. See ya. [turns to walk away]
He'll view it as a challenge when he's getting his ass kicked!
Shut up, fatass!!

How??
[sighs] Not like that!
Fine!
Come on, Tweek! He's only got one arm!

This is when you gotta get mean, Tweek.
Go, Tweek. Kick his ass! Get him!
Get him! [the fighters just pant, stuck to each other] Whoa, Tweek! Did you hear that?

That people shouldn't sue each other all the time.
[bursting in] Wait! [Stan, Cartman, and Peetie follow]

[walks up with Butters] What's the matter?
Uh oh. I guess we shouldn't have made him eat it. [Stan jumps back as Kenny starts vomiting the spleen up. Stan and Kyle watch in shock]
Aw, dude! You can still kinda see the spleen! [Butters looks at him] How much, Kenny?
I'll give you five bucks to eat your puke.
That's 19 bucks, Kenny! [more kids gather]
Kick ass, dude!

Whoa! [the others look stunned]
What did they do with all the fat? There must have been enough to last an Eskimo family months.
Dude. I don't know if I'm going to like the new Eric Cartman.

[he and Stan look at Jesus for a moment] Huh? Why not?
I don't know.
Why?
Cartman, what the hell's the matter with you? [takes a donut]
Alright, Ms. Crabtree. Is it comf'table enough?
Six hours.
Great.
For what?

[sits next to the new Cartman. Stan sits by Kyle's other side] He worked so hard, come so close. Now we'll never see Kenny crawl up into Ms. Crabtree's uterus.

...Alright, that does it! [rises and backs up a bit] This has been bothering the hell out of me! [reaches for the new Cartman's cap and pulls it off, revealing a puffy head of hair. Stan registers shock] I knew it! You're not Cartman at all!
Don't worry, dude. You're gonna do great.
Oh, you're doing it, or else we're gonna bust your whole scheme wide open, and tell your mom you haven't actually been at your drug rehab this whole time!
Yeah. They've kinda killed Kenny -'s look-alike. You bastards!
Come on. Throw the football, Ike.
Hepatitis B?
...You got Raging Pussies tickets??
[withdraws] Hold on. I'll be right back. [turns and runs into the house]
Mom, Dad, can I go with the guys to see the Raging Pussies?
But all the guys are going!
But Mom, I-
Ugh! [turns right and walks out]
My parents said I can't go.
[looks down] Ah. Oh, now I already told them.
No! It's alright! Just give me some time to work on them. I'll see you guys later. [turns and runs back into the house. Ike finally throws the football off and looks out from the snow]
...But what if I do a bunch of chores around the house? Come on, you're being unfair!
What's Cuba?
And do I have to shovel the whole driveway, or just the side the car is on?
Hoh, geez. [walks away]
Dear Mr. Castro: My name is Kyle. [thinks] I am an eight-year-old American boy who lives in South Park.

And if I had just one wish, just one wish in the whole world, If I had one wish it'd be for Cuba to change. [Castro sees a drawing of a sad Kyle holding a flower, which fades to a sad Kyle writing his letter] Because I think that all the Cubans are in pain All the joy in the world, from sea to shining sea [Kyle finishes a drawing of a sad rainbow coalition atop a world globe] Doesn't mean a thing if Cubans aren't free [Castro see a drawing of a sad Kyle inside a small house] I just can't be very happy, that's certain [A picture of Kyle replaces his self-portrait on the paper] Not as long as your Cubans are hurtin' [Kyle finishes one last drawing of himself, which Castro sees last] Oh, won't you search your soul and find a way to change your mind? That is my one and only wish.
[exults] I did it! Now I can go to the Raging Pussies!
[wounded, turns] What??
But I did! Ah, I brought democracy to Cuba!
But that's not fair! You lied to me!
What I understand is that you totally screwed me over!! So why should I have to listen to you?!
Well I wish I didn't have any parents! [walks to the front door, opens it, and exits, shocking Gerald and Sheila]
It's so unfair! How can my parents do that to me?!
They're evil! I WISH I DIDN'T HAVE ANY PARENTS!
How?!
What's that?
[awed] Wow! Three months without parents!
Who cares? My parents deserve whatever they get. They're liars and cheats.
[straight] "My parents molestered me."
What's "bad touch"?
Okay, molestered, bad touch.
Cool, thanks.
...Nothing.
Not one adult left?
[emerges from the group and stands next to Stan] Yeah. [these two head Treasure Cove]
The fatass. The mayor.
Because we do. It was like this yesterday, and the day before that.
Sure, outlander. I'll get it [starts to move...]
Parents. Mom. Dad.
Yeah. I guess their rules did have a point. Things have gotten a lot worse in the ten days since they've been gone.
Here's our cell phone, dude. [hands it to Mark] Will you call the police for us? [Mark begins dialing]
Do you think they're gonna pissed at us for lying that they molested us and sending them all to jail for ten days?
Did you make it to your job interview?
Well, thanks for everything, you guys. You really helped us see how important parents are.
Mom! Dad!
Yeah. We're fine.
But you didn't do anything to me.
[lags] But, you guys, I--
Huh.
Sure. [the boys turn left and start walking]

Heee might not come if you're too close to the toilet bowl, Ike. [lifts him off the seat and takes him back to the night stand] Come sit by me. [they sit down and face the toilet bowl, and wait. Nothing happens.]
Just let us stay up a little longer, mom. Mr. Hankey's gotta show up. He always does.
Happy Chanukah, Mom. [returns his sight to the toilet bowl and waits...]
Go away!
[barks. Music stops] Stan! Go get the other guys and tell them to meet me at the bus stop in ten minutes!
Okay, good. You're all here.
It's Mr. Hankey! He hasn't shown up yet.
It's only three days until Christmas, you guys! You know how bad things have been around here. I think it might be because Mr. Hankey hasn't come.
If you guys want there to be a Christmas, you'd better come help me!
[turns and glares at Cartman] Dude, you sneezed on my back!
Hey, look. [before them is a small cottage in a collection basin. They walk to the end of the sewer line] Hello?

Sure we'll help! [Stan grins]
Jesus, this sucks! All they keep doin' is dancing around!
Hey, that's it. Oh, my God, that's totally it! [drops down from the sofa and walks to the TV] It's so simple!

[turns and faces the other boys] We can get everyone back into the Christmas spirit by making our very own animated Christmas special, and showing it to everybody in town! [Charlie and Linus talk onscreen]

[as the boys enter]Mayor! We have the solution to your problem.

[to the other three] You guys go tell Butters to start making the cutoouts. I'm gonna go tell Mr. Hankey the good news!
[now facing the house from the sewer] Ah, Mr. Hankey?

God job, Butters.

What's a hard p?

We wish-   [the sound man presses a few buttons, and some white noise blasts through the boys' headphones]
What?

Dreidel dreidel dreidel, I made you out of clay, Dreidel dreidel dreidel--
[throws his headphones off and faces Cartman angrily] Don't you oppress me, fat boy.

Check it out, dude. The camera shoots one frame at a time. So, all we gotta do, is put the right mouth on, according to what syllable they're pronouncing at that frame.

Okay. So we put little "woo" mouths on all our heads. [sets the "woo" mouths in place] And then we shoot that for one frame.
That's one twenty-fourth of a second of our movie already shot! [exults]
Now, the next mouth.
Okay, where are the E-mouths?
Okay. "Woo" mouths again?
So how much done is that?
[softly] Aw, [loudly] Jesus Christ!
Okay. Okay, the shot is finally set up. Now shoot the O mouth for two frames. [Cartman sneezes and immediately realizes what he just did]
Cartman!
[rushing to the door] Fine! We'll do it with out you!
We'll dub his voice over.

Now, don't go saying that. There's always hope. Miracles happen most every day.  To people like you, and me. But don't expect a miracle. Unless you help make it to be.  You hope, and I'll hurry. [takes the poster and rolls it up.] You pray, and I'll plan [The boys exit the Photo Dojo with it] We'll do what's necessary, 'cause [now in Stan's room, works on a Brian Boitano cutout] Even a miracle needs a hand! You love-

[stops and looks back] I'm going to the kitchen! This is stupid!

You guys! You guys! I've looked up the word, "shit"! I think it might have something to do with people dying!

I am not full of meecro- what? Look, the word "shit" first showed up in English in the 1340s, the same time as something called, "The Black Death".

[holds his left palm out] No no! The word, "shit".

Cartman, stop being an asshole! [camera pans left to the lead knight sitting between two men, reading from THE WORLD NEWS. The knight lowers the paper and looks over at the boys, then sips from his coffee cup]

That's 15 people we got to agree to come see David Blaine perform in Denver.

This is a really good turnout.

Dude, no way! [two female Blaintology assistants rush up and help Blaine stand. One has a little cage, another has a small curtain and rod. Mass suicide?
[whispering] Cartman! Cartman, wake up! Cartman!

Okay. Okay, you're right. [goes down the ladder to his own bunk, underneath Cartman's, and Cartman turns over to sleep] Oh uh Cartman: thanks. [goes to sleep. [He tries to move, but encounters the glass. He taps to make sure] What the hell? [Camera pulls back to reveal...]
What have you done, Cartman?!
[knocking on the dome] Cartman, you fatass tattle-tale!
Cartman! We've been brainwashed, don't you see? We don't have to do this!
Cartman, no!
[off-screen] You bastards!
[off-screen] You bastards! [Stan looks up and follows Kyle's voice]
Stan!
I don't want to kill myself. They rigged this thing to fill with water! [tremulous footsteps are felt, and Lincoln is shown walking among the crowd of Blaintologists]
Wagh. [sits up]
Thanks for saving us Stan. You're my Super Best Friend.
[moves away so Stan can have a turn] Haha, hehahaha.
What the hell are you so happy about, fatass? [Cartman gets off his bike]
...What the hell are you talking about?
What's "pubes"?
Oh. [to Cartman] No you didn't!
[turns to look at them] Hell no! [Stan and Kenny turn to look]
[approaches] Uh, what are those? [Stan and Kenny follow]
Scott Tenorman? The ninth grader?
Cartman, you don't buy pubes, you grow them yourself!
Yuh huh!
Because, retard, you're dumb enough to buy Scott Tenorman's pubes for ten dollars!
Yeah.
Cartman, can I give you some advice?
Just let it go, dude. You only had sixteen dollars and twelve cents. Count your losses and move on. He's smarter than you.
One please.
Scott Tenorman is an eighth grader who sold Cartman his pubes for ten dollars, and now Cartman's all pissed off.
What's in it for us?
Okay, Cartman, what do you want?
[rolls his eyes] Oh, Jesus!
Okay, so what's the plan?
...What?
You're such a dumbass, Cartman. [he and Stan turn and walk away]
[voice at other end] Scott Tenorman?
We just wanna warn you: Eric Cartman, the fourth grader, is going' to try and trick you somehow into getting your wiener bitten off by a pony who lives at Denkins' ranch.
'Cause, we're his friends.
'Cause we hate him.
Well, we just thought we'd let you know. See ya.
Oho, we will. Trust us. We won't miss this. [looks at Stan, who's smiling]
Yeah, sure. [As Chef arrives, Stan and Kyle leave]
Dude, I think it might be best for us to never piss Cartman off again.

[not turning around, voice quivering] Do you know what happened to me this morning, Stan? This morning... I woke up and felt a sharp pain in my ass. [leaves the pew to face Stan, teary-eyed] Do you?! Do you, Stan?! Because all my life I was raised to believe in Jehovah! Hohohooho! Oowwww!
[bawling] Hoh Gohod, I popped it!! Oh hit huhurts!!

[now standing, rubbing his ass and wailing] Stan, I have to go home!! I need my cream!! I need my creeheam!!
My life can't get any worse!
Lucky. [the operating room doors open and in walks Stan]

[rolls his eyes] Oh no...
Dude, this is unbearable.
Aw dude, this is really hard.
Throw 'em away! [the boys' faces are red. Kyle glances back] Dudes, here he comes. Guys, stop coughing. [the boys stifle their coughs as Mr. Mackey draws near.]
[looks] D'awww sick! [Stan coughs and tries to cover his mouth]
Oh God... [looks down. One of the parents knocks.]
[seizing the opportunity] Yeah. This is really their fault.
[to Stan] Who's Rob Reiner?
You guys, maybe we should come clean right now and tell everyone that it wasn't the tobacco companies that made us want to smoke.

Well it's just that, eh, this seems like another one of those times when things are gonna get way out of hands, you know? It's been happening a lot lately. How about this time we just put a stop to it right now?
Oh no...
But... isn't that, kind of, lying?
What??
So, tobacco helped to build America.
That sounds perfectly reasonable.
But dude, you're making stuff up.
Guys, I think we should bail out of this right now!

This is just startin' to look like another one of those times where it-it's gonna end up with the whole town turning out, it's a big showdown happening, and us havin' to talk about what we learned, and I say we just stop right now, and go play cards or something.
Go ahead. We don't wanna be in their stupid commercial.
No, we really want nothing more to do with these people.
What are you doing? [Cartman snaps his head around and looks]

Cartman, you go ahead and do the commercial tomorrow. But I'm warning you, those anti-smoking people are liars and they're bullies who will stop at nothing to get what they want, and that means they're dangerous. [walks around Cartman, opens the door, goes under lumber obstruction, enters the bedroom, then closes the door. Cartman is a bit surprised]
Who's going to kill you?
Yeah dude, don't get us killed too. [the boys leave the table]
[the other boys back away] No dude, get away!
Yeah! Go to the tobacco company yourself!
Yeah dude. You were totally wrong.
No! What we really should do is go to our parents right now and take responsibility for smoking ourselves. Even if it means getting grounded.

Because, if we go to the tobacco company, I know exactly what'll happen. They'll take us in, and then Rob Reiner will show up with all the townspeople, holding torches or something, and there'll be a big showdown until we talk about what we learned, and change everyone's minds - this is all following a formula!
God-damnit! [Cartman hides behind Mr. Harris upon seeing Rob Reiner]
No it isn't, you fat turd! Because, I've learned something today. You just hate- [to Stan] See, I knew it.
You just hate smoking, so you use all your money and power to force others to think like you. And that's called fascism, you tubby asshole!
No.
No we didn't, dude! No we didn't! [walks off]
Yeah! Like Stan gives a crap if Wendy breaks up! [The boys get back into their playing positions. A few moments Kyle looks back] Stan? [Clyde looks back, then Cartman]
[not looking up] Why?
Aw, dude, come on. I gotta do my science homework.
[puts his book down and sighs] God damn it! [walks over to Wendy, but avoids eye contact] Wendy, Stan wants to know why you break up. [Wendy turns around]
'Kay. [walks back to Stan, but avoids looking at him, as well] She says she's been wantin' to break up for a while, and it's nothing against you.
[goes for his books and picks them up] No dude, I'm out. Go talk to her yourself. Be poetic. [walks off. Jimmy appears]
Stan, you can't keep doing this to yourself. You have to go live.
Dude, not now! [Cartman looks down, embarrassed]
Jeez, he's worse than I thought.
No. We just have to show him that there's other girls out there. I say we take him to Raisins.
What do you think, Stan. These girls are pretty cute, huh?

Hey. Hey, look over there, Stan. That Raisins girl is really cute, huh? [a Raisins girl walks by with long black hair] Why don't you say hi to her? [calls out] Excuse me? [motions for her to come over]
Hey. Uh, this is Stan.
Okay. Okay, come on you guys. [they all hop off their seats and walk off]
Look, we're just trying to show you there's other girls out there.
What are you doing?
[returns] Come on, Stan. We're gonna play dodgeball.
Dude, you need to snap out of this! So Wendy left you for Tolkien. What are you gonna do? Just be miserable your whole life?
Aw, come on, dude! All you've done for the last four days is mope around! You might as well hang out with those Goth kids who dress in black and talk about pain all the time!
Oh Jesus Christ, I had to see it to believe it! What the hell are you doing?!
God-damnit dude, your mom and dad want you to come home!
Oh, like you know what pain is! Go try living in a Third-World country, you little pussy!
Stan, this is it. Time to stop feeling sorry for yourself and come home! Everyone cares about you and everyone wants you back!
Yeah. She is.
[walks away, defeated] Fine. That's it. I give up. Have fun being miserable.
[prepares to receive the football] Okay, it's third down. And now, somebody make a play!
What happened? Aren't you still wallowing in pain?
Well. Dude, it's uh it's good to have you back.
No Ike! Shh!
[frightened] Ike's not my little brother anymore?
Ike, you'll always be my little brother, okay?

You'd better! [Harry closes the car door and goes to his side, then settles in to drive. The car lunges forward on square wheels. Kyle looks as Ike goes away. Ike looks back] Dad, can't we talk to this new Canadian Prime Minister? If he knew the situation, he might be-
Guys. [the other boys turn to face him] Guys, I need your help.
It's been a week since Ike's been gone, and every day my parents seem worse. I have to try to go to Canada and speak with the new Canadian Prime Minister, but I can't do it alone.
Please, you guys, you don't understand. [walks off some distance] My family is devastated. My mom just walks around the house like a zombie, and my dad can't stop crying.
[returns] I found the number for a really cheap airline to Canada. If we go as soon as possible, then-
What?
[to Stan] Is that true?

I'm sorry you guys, but there is something we can do. We can go to Canada and see the Prime Minister like I said. If we can change his mind before Christmas, then your parents won't have to give my family money.
It's worth a shot. Come on, you guys, we can do this.
[reassuring] We'll get back in time for a Christmas adventure.
Uh, I must have the wrong number. We were trying to reach City Airlines.
Uh, we need to go to Canada. As soon as possible.
Four.
How about fifty daura?
Fifty-five daura.
Okay. Sixty daura.
Okay.
Got it. [hangs up]
Why not?
You're not gonna die, Kenny. Don't be stupid.
All right! We're going to Canada!
Hey, where the hell are you going?? [Mr. Kim jumps out and away. A few seconds later he pulls the rip cord and the parachute comes out]
I'm trying! [the plane bounces around in the air]
No.
Hey! We're in Canada!
Uh. My adopted brother got taken back here to Canada? So, we want to talk to the new Canadian Prime Minister about getting him back?
Who's that?
Look, we don't have a lot of time here, okay? Can you just tell us where the new Prime Minister is?
So how do we get to Ottawa?
Word!
Who are you?
That's okay, we'd rather just go by ourselves.
French Canada?
We don't have time for this.
Hello?
Okay, you can come with us.
God-damnit, we need to get to the new Prime Minister! NOW!
Can we just get going, please?
There's no way we can go all the way back. We'll never make it now!
Well come on! [everyone hops into the boat]
Do you think we can still make it in time?
We need to see the new Prime Minister.
No. No!! [knocks on the door again. Steve and the Mime turn around]
Please, sir. I traveled a long way to get here. He's the only person who can help me.
[turns around and walks off slowly] Then that's it. I'm... I'm never going to get my brother back. [sits down on the steps farther away from the door]
[turns around] Really? [the boys stand and approach the doors]
[after a few moments, steps forth] Sir, you recently passed a new law allowing parents who have given their children up for adoption to change their minds. My little brother was-
Ike!

Please, sir. I came because I don't think Ike belongs here. Family isn't about whose blood you have in you, family is about the people who cared about you and took care of you. We're not the same blood, but I love my little brother. We've taken care of him because he needed us to, and that makes us more family than anything. [Harry and Elise look at each other]
But why are you making such strange laws??

[walks over to the charred remains] You... bastards! [brushes off a bit of Kenny from his jacket] Wha, what the hell is wrong with you?? What kind of Prime Minister bases his decisions on hatred? [Stan dusts himself off] And, and takes away mounties' horses? [Stan notices a purple curtain nearby and walks over to it] And French people's wine? What the hell kind of Prime Minister are you, anyway?!
[the other members of the group gather in, as well as other people nearby] What the hell??
Well yeah, but ah-I got my brother back.
Dude, come on.
[stops so he doesn't get hurt and glares] Stop it, Cartman!
[stops] Goddammit Cartman, stop throwin' those stupid poppy-things at me! [Cartman cackles some more. The boys approach a booth: Roger's Edge]
[softly] Wow, cool.
[turns away] Our parents won't let us have weapons, dude. [the others turn as well]
Why do people have to keep reminding us of what we don't have?!
Kaii yo! [one end of his nunchaku hits his hat a few times]
Yeah. And my powerful nunchakus make me into Bunroku [he transforms], a deadly but compassionate ninja who protects those in trouble.
[cautions] No dude, we can't go around showing our weapons to people. Our parents'll find out we have them.
[the background is a motion blur] You don't know anything about Jews, fatass!
I still say this is a bad idea.
But don't tell anybody we have them.
Okay, hang on guys. I'll use my special power to see into the future and find out where we should head next.
God dammit, Cartman! You can't keep making up new powers!
No asshole! From now on you only get to have one power! So what is it?!
That doesn't count, fatass!
Who the hell is that?
Whoa.

Well, let's see how he likes the icy blasts from my nunchucks of Sokuromoto! [whips them around a few times and unleashes an icy stream of energy towards Butters. The blasts knock Butters out of the air and he hits the ground with a thud.]
Okay, okay, you can have your powers back.
God dammit Cartman!
What the hell did you do that for, Kenny?!
Oh man! We are in serious trouble!
I agree with Cartman!
You don't understand what my mom will do to me if she finds out I was playing with weapons!
Stop dude! You're gonna scramble his brain!
If we take him to the hospital, they're gonna find out what happened.
[moves off] God? Please, if you get me out of this, I swear, I will never play with weapons ever again.
Oh no.
That is the dumbest idea you guys have ever come up with! I'd expect this stupidity out of Cartman, but you, Stan?! Butters needs medical attention right now!

We need some more fur. [Stan walks over to Sparky and shaves off fur from areas of his body still unshaved, then walks back to Kyle and hands him the fur. Kyle places the fur on Butters' left leg] I think that's good.
We've gotta hurry, it's getting late! [some trash bin noises are heard and the boys face the source of the noises]
Quick, hide Butters! [Cartman drags Butters to an oven]
He said, not now, Craig!
I swore to never fight again.
Oh no. Butters!
[approaches Craig] Butters! He got a ninja star stuck in his eye, and we were taking him to the vet when you fucked it all up! Butters!
Butters!
Hey Butters!
Dude, look! [a black man walks up in anime form, stops, and looks around]
Uuuh, Chef, you haven't seen Butters around, have you?
Yeah, we know.
Butters!
It's hopeless, dude! Butters must have made it to the hospital. By now our parents probably know we were playing with weapons! We have to get rid of the evidence! [moves off]
[reaches a well and holds his nunchucks over it] Dude, we have to get rid of our weapons so at least we can try to deny everything.
We don't have time for that, dude! We just have to ditch them! Now!
Screw you, fatass! [struggles to loosen his grip on the nunchucks]
[walks up next to Stan] I- I can't do it... I can't do it. I...
Listen, doucher! Our parents are gonna kill us, and you, if they found out that we bought these!
Where?!
Then it's not too late!
We have to get past them!
You have that power too?
Oh dude, we are gonna get it now.
Dude, they don't care we knocked Butters' eye out with weapons?
[looks around, then stands on his chair] Uh, yeah! I agree! Uh- my fragile little eight-year-old mind didn't know how to deal with what I was seeing. C-Cartman should be punished!
Yeah, I c- I can't believe it.
[pulls out his nunchucks] So I guess this means we get to keep our weapons.
They're Olympic games for handicapped people.
Yeah, that'd be cool.
Well all right, we'll see you on Saturday, guys.
...You're an asshole, Cartman.
What?
Oh no. Cartman, no!
[moves and catches up to Cartman] Cartman! I will not stand by and let you cheat your way to winning the Special Olympics!
Because! [takes away the brochure]
[low voice] God damn you!
No you're not! [whips out the brochure] I read the brochure, Cartman! If you're under eighteen, you have to have a parent with you to sign up for the Special Olympics.

It says right there "a parent has to be with you to sign up," and you'll never get your mom to agree to something so horrible, so ha! [grins confidently. Cartman looks at him, then at the brochure and reads]
Cartman, I really, really have a problem with what you're doing. I object to it morally, and I find it grossly offensive. [they look at each other and Cartman closes a book he had open for reference]

I know that I often have serious moral objections to the things that you do, but... this time I think you really need to reconsider, because if you do this, I believe you will go to hell. So I feel it is my responsibility, as your friend, to tell people what you're doing, and to put a stop to it!
I didn't come here to talk about The Passion, Cartman!
I came here to talk about you!
I'm a Vulcan!
[looking into an imaginary viewer] The atmosphere is oxygen-based, should support our breathing.
No! I'm on the away team too! [he and Kenny remove their belts]
I don't care! You're not making me wait in the van again!
I am picking up carbon-based life forms in Sector C. I believe we will find a village of peaceful aliens over that ridge. [Cartman sighs silently]
[stops firing and stands still] No it doesn't. [the other boys continue with their phaser noises]
No I'm not! God damn it Cartman, you're not gonna kill me off again!
Shut up about Jews, fatass! You don't know anything!
He does not!
Naw uh!
I'm not arguing about The Passion! He's being an asshole!
People don't hate the Jews!
...You're a stupid asshole! [turns and walks off. Cartman turns left and glances at Kyle]
One please.
Yeah, I know, but I have to-
...Thanks. [makes his way towards the doors, glancing back at the cashier in wonder]
Haaaah! [Next scene has Kyle with his eyes squeezed shut and his hands over his face. He's now curled up in a ball]
How? How could the Jews do that to Jesus?
You were right. You were right all along. I thought you were just an asshole when you ripped on Jews, but... I didn't know, I... I didn't know.
You were, you were right?
You were right. [Cartman opens his eyes and beams brightly]

Kill Jesus! Yesss! Arrrgh! [a spear pierces Jesus' side. The one piercing him is Kyle himself, who seems to be relishing this, as he pierces Jesus a few more times. A review of images, then an image of Alan Alda, and Kyle wakes up frightened. After a few screams he looks around]
Oh okay, but did God sent Jesus TO die, or did Jesus just get kind of screwed over.
Well, I have this friend, see? And this friend belongs to a certain, Chosen People of Israel. And it... so happens that these chosen people killed your Lord.

Right. But he can't live with the guilt anymore. Because, even if Jesus wasn't really the Son of God, he was still a nice guy. And he didn't deserve what happened to him in Mel Gibson's movie. I I can't sleep at night. I mean, my... friend can't sleep at night.
But how can the Jews make it better??
Wait. That's it. Atonement. Of course. [gets off the chair] I know what I have to do now. Thank you, Father. [turns and walks out]

Thank you, rabbi. [Sheila smiles and gets Gerald's attention. Kyle clears his throat.] In 1973, the United States officially issued an apology to the African American community for slavery. In 1956, Germany officially apologized for World War II AND the Holocaust. And now, I believe, in 2004, the Jewish community needs to apologize for the death of Jesus.
If we as a people choose not to believe that Jesus is the Son of God, then we can still apologize for the brutal way in which he was killed, and take our share of the responsibility for it.
I saw The Passion!
[to his parents] Both you guys, stop! Please. You're gonna make people hate us more!
[facing the congregants] No, no, no! Don't become an angry mob! [behind him Cartman is seen leading his mob to the theater] The last time we did that we killed Jesus!

[noticing] Look out!! [The crowds move to the other side of the street as the tour bus skids to a stop just past the theater. Mel Gibson roars into town and crashes into the ticket booth, and his gas truck blows up. The crowds crawl out of their safety places and merge]
[joins Stan and Kenny] Dude, what's wrong with him?
Dude! I've been freaked out this whole time because of that guy's movie?
Oh, dude, I feel so much better about being Jewish now that I see that Mel Gibson is just a big wacko douche. [a grinning Mel squats and farts on Cartman, defecating on Cartman]

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: Sweet. I made mine go off the jump. [Stan's car is uncooperative]

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: Hey, who are those kids?

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: ...What the hell just happened?

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: Yeah.

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: Dude, that is a sweet RC car!

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: We're not interested, thanks.

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: Yeah! Go Stan!

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: All right Stan!

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: Yeah! You got served!

Episode Title: You Got F'd in the A
Lines: That's right!
What the hell are you doing, fatass?
Why?
Why?
Oh wait. Hey AWESOM-O, [Cartman stops] I'd also like some celery sticks chopped up two inches long, with peanut butter and raisins on top.
Yeah, I think they already moved in. I saw moving vans in their driveway two days ago.
[points] Hey Look!
Hey. Do you live here?
Dude, he just be loaded! What does he do?
[softly] What's wrong with his face?
Mr. Jefferson, your son can't get up.
Mr. Jefferson?
Mr. Jefferson said we can invite all the kids in town to go play over at their house.
Dude, what happened to your knee?
[calls out] Mr. Jefferson!
Mr-! Goddammit. Here, come on. We need to clean that up. [takes Blanket inside]
Alright, this is gonna sting for a second.
I know, I know. Be cool.
So, dude, do you have any brothers or sisters?
And where is your mom?
You must have a mom.
You mean she doesn't live here, or she's dead, or what?
What?
So you never met your mom?
Yeah. Yeah, that counts.
You guys, I feel kinda bad for that kid.
Mr. Jefferson just seems like he wants to be a kid, not have one.
They're TV dinners. Don't you wanna take that veil off so you can eat?
Dude, look who I found prowling around in my back yard.
He was out all alone in the middle of the night. Mr. Jefferson isn't even home.
What?!
Come on, Blanket.
[stops] That poor kid.
Hey Blanket. Uh, look, we're goin' over to help my dad chop wood. You... wanna come with?
[the boys fear for Blanket's life] Jesus Christ, dude!
Dude, we have got to get that kid away from him!
All right. Thanks a lot for helping us, dude.
[seething as he climbs the ladder] I don't think Mr. Jefferson pays enough attention to his son to notice. Come on! [Stan and Kenny follow]
Shh, Blanket, we're gonna take you away for a little while, okay? [Kenny looks around]
Come on, Blanket! We gotta go before your dad sees us.
You bastard!
[grabs Blanket's hand and leaves as well] Come on!
[Kyle and Stan help Blanket up] Hang on, Blanket!

[returns with Blanket] All right, let's just say all the bad things said about Mr. Jefferson are lies! Let's say the police department does just go around spending their time framing people for crimes they didn't commit! Let's say it's all made up, and Mr. Jefferson is just a nice guy who's trying to be a child because he never got to have a childhood. Well that's fine, except for that he HAS children now! And when people have children, they have to grow up!
All right! Things just might work out!
You've been on your fucking phone since we started!
A break from what?! You haven't done anything!
All you ever do is talk about your balls!
If you want your share of the money, then you're gonna shovel snow like the rest of us!
Twenty-five cents? Well that's not even worth it.
Dude. [the camera pulls back to show these immigrants shoveling snow off sidewalks and driveways up and down the street]
What?!
Dude, hold on! This is bullcrap! If they wanna live in our time, then they should learn our language!
Aw, dude.
[drops his shovel] This is really gay.
Wait. You guys, I have an awesome idea! We should secretly go around and tell all the students we can, to not check any of the mascots on this election sheet, and instead write in "Giant Douche."
Turd Sandwich isn't better than Giant Douche.
It was my idea and we're gonna tell everyone to write in "Giant Douche!" It's way funnier!
Kenny, what's funnier? A giant douche or a turd sandwich?
Stan, do you pick giant douche or turd sandwich?
[tallies the votes. Behind him, Butters approaches his locker and prepares to open it] That's two against one, 'cause Stan doesn't care. So it's giant douche.
You hate Butters.
You misled him, fatass!
Jimmy, we're gonna have everyone write in a mascot that's really funny, and you have to tell us which one would be funnier.
A giant douche.
Giant douche.
A giant douche.
All right, it's decided. Let's all write in "Giant Douche."
Cartman? What the hell?!
You won't get more votes than us, asshole!
Be sure to vote for Giant Douche.
Giant Douche is your man!

Dude, I'm not going to lose to Cartman's stupid turd sandwich. [something like an ice cream truck is heard, and Cartman appears driving his Big Wheels bike, pulling a portable stage. Butters is dancing on the stage, dressed as a Hawaiian hula dancer. In his hands he has leis to hand out.]
There. Do you really want that asshole to win?
What? Y-you gotta vote, dude. Haven't you seen the Rock the Vote stuff or, or Puff Daddy's Vote or Die?!
Kenny, we have got to make Stan understand the importance of voting, because he'll definitely vote for our guy.
You're doing the right thing, Stan. Don't you feel like you're a part of something now?
Look, it may not seem important now, but your vote really does count, and we all have to do our part.
Woah... wait, what are you doing?
No, no, you... you wrote down Turd Sandwich.
...Dude, you're supposed to vote for Giant Douche.
Well yeah, but not if your decision is for Turd Sandwich! What the hell is wrong with you?!
Well, I just figured you'd vote for my guy! Who's fuckin' friend are you?! [calls out to] Puffy!
Stan, don't you think this has gone far enough? Is it really that big a deal? [Stan sighs, but says nothing more in response] Yeah, just vote. For Giant Douche.
Ha! You lose, fatass!
That is fucking stupid, Cartman!
Hey! Isn't there where Stark's Pond used to be? Where we used to kayak and fish?
Why the hell would you want three copies of the same movie?
You only need one copy, r-tard!
Okay, fine, I will! [grabs a copy] H-wait a minute! I don't even want one copy of Time Cop! [puts it back]
Dude, I can't deal with Wall-Mart right now. My parents had me there for three hours last night. [they pass by a man closing up his shop for the last time]
Why, Mr. Farkle?
[glares at Cartman] Cartman, stop it!
See?! That sucks, dude!

Yeah, but what about all the people getting laid off from the grocery stores? [Cartman whips out the violin and plays it again] And what about all the- [looks at Cartman, takes away his violin, breaks it in half using his leg, and throws the pieces to the ground]

What the hell? [before them is a downtown that is shuttered and decayed. The asphalt is gone from the roads and eagles hover over the area. A window crashing makes them jump, and Butters appears around a corner, making weird noises.]
Butters? What the hell are you doing?
But you run the Wall-Mart.
You hate Wall-Mart, too? [rumbles emanate from the walls]
No! All we have to do is not shop at Wall-Mart anymore! If you want it to go away, all it takes is a little self-control and personal responsibility.
[looking at Cartman] It wasn't my idea to burn the Wall-Mart down.
Dude, our town is going to be better without the- [sounds of construction are heard. Kyle turns to look. ] What the?

How... How did this happen? [the other boys make their way to the store, then look around at the restored store, which is running as if nothing had happened the night before. Kyle's parents are shopping there, and they run into the boys.] Mom, Dad? Why are you shopping here?
Hey! Hey! [the driver looks at them] Who the hell told you to put this thing back up?!
But nobody wants a Wall-Mart here!
Looks like we're gonna have to go to Arkansas. Come on, guys. We're gonna put a stop to Wall-Mart once and for all!
No way! You wanna go with us so you can betray us at some point and keep us from destroying the Wall-Mart.
Yeah, huh! You wanna go with us so that later you go, "Haha! I was working for Wall-Mart all along!" or something.
All right, fine. Come on, fatass! [leaves to catch up with Stan.]
[rushes out to face Cartman] I heard that!
You said we have no idea that you're never let us hurt Wall-Mart!
He is working for the Wall-Mart to stop us from succeeding!
God-damnit! [turns and heads towards Stan]
It would've been faster if Cartman hadn't slashed the tires!
Yeah. We've come to complain. We don't want a Wall-Mart in our town.
We want to talk to who's in charge.
So how do we stop it?
The heart of Wall-Mart?
All right. C'mon you guys. We have to get back home. [they drop down and leave the room]
All right, this is it! If Wall-Mart has a heart, we have to find it and destroy it! No matter what the Wall-Mart does to try to stop us, we have to be strong! Let's do it.
I knew you were!
Yes, I did! I said from the beginning that you would do this!
Yes, I did!
Yes, I did!
Yes, I did!
Yes. I did! [a few more rounds of this and they stand head to head, silent]
[interrupting] -slashed the bus tires in Arkansas! I said so! I told you the minute that I- [Cartman babbles loudly to drown him out] -and I told you that-
[he and Stan walk around Cartman] We don't have time for this! Kenny, keep him away from us! [Kenny does as told]
We've gotta find the television department. [the lights flicker and turn off. Randy leaps into view in front of the boys, carrying an ax. Stan and Kyle scream]
I think I see the television department in the back!
Who are you?
Where's the heart?
The question is, "Where is the heart?"
The Wall-Mart is imploding! Everybody out NOW! [the shoppers and employees now bolt for the doors and run out as an M in Mart falls down.]
All Wall-Marts start a self-destruction sequence if you break a mirror in the back.
Duh.
Okay, hang on a second I-
All right, all right! [Stan pulls him further away until there's no one around them] Dude, what is the matter with you?
Trent Boyett?! The kid from preschool?!
Oh, no! No!
Trent Boyett is being released from Juvenile Hall.
Yeah.
Look, maybe he's forgiven us. I mean, we were only in preschool.
Totally, dude, let's play Fireman.
Shut up, fat ass!

[irritated] Just stop it! [at the top of his lungs] Stoop iiit!! [the lights go out as the bulbs shatter, then the shelf above his bed falls and everything on it hits the floor. The psychics and Cartman stop their battle and witness all this] There's a logical explanation for that.

[looks down] No. [walks towards the manger] No, I want to have the Antichrist inside me!

[returns to the altar, climbs up, and exults] Yes, yes! Now the Jews shall take control of Christmas once and for all! HAHA! HAAA!!

[leaves the room and goes up the stairs, stopping halfway] I'm never speaking to either of you ever again! [continues up the stairs and goes to his room. His door is heard being shut. Gerald looks on as all this happens]

Cartman!

[turns around and returns to Cartman, then says between gritted teeth calmly but angrily] I am going to break everything that you own. [spins around and walks away]

What hope?!

Magic Johnson?

[moments later] Thank you for seeing us, Mr. Johnson. We were hoping that maybe you have some kind of key that can help us with our disease.
['[quickly irritated via short temper exploding] Will you stop it with that!?! [angrily points at Cartman] What part of this is funny to you?!! ']

[angrily points at Cartman again] Then stop saying you're not just sure, you're HIV positive!! [Cartman keeps quiet] This isn't funny, AIDS isn't funny, dying isn't funny, [points at Cartman a third time with his eyes closed.] So shut the fuck up!!
[angrily points at Cartman a fourth time] Knock it off!! Right now!! This isn't funny!! At all!!
[quickly] Yes!!!
Well I've been thinking: maybe there's something you've come into contact with that hinders HIV from growing. Do you mind if we just look around?
But everyone tries that. There has to be something you're exposed to that others aren't. Could we see where you sleep?
Dude.
You sleep with money. Every night?

[looks away] Wugh.

A hundred thousand dollars?

A hundred thousand for a picture of Britney peeing on a ladybug. Imagine what a photo of her crapping on a squirrel is worth!

[he and Stan are blinded by the flash] Dude! [the doctor reaches the curtains and closes them, but the flashes don't stop going off]

What?!

Platform 4F. Uhhh, it must be on the other side of the station.

NO!

Mom, Dad! [runs up to them] They're gonna kill her! They're going to in-. Wait, what are you doing here?
Be a good boy? You know all about this?

Corn harvest!

Dad? Dad! What the hell are you doing?!
[eyes closed] I have no idea.

Yeah. [Kenny begins to grab more flowers with gusto to get more of their aroma. The other boys get worried] He's getting... really high on life. [Kenny begins to snort and grabs all the flowers he can, treating them just as he did the cats earlier.]
[runs to Kenny] Kenny! [Stan and Cartman follow. Kenny falls in Kyle's arms, goes into spasms, and then freezes, his eyes unfocused]
Kenny? Kenny?!
Guys, I'm really worried about my brother.
You should care! This strike affects everybody, fatass!
There aren't gonna be new shows! Don't you get it?! Terrance and Phillip are Canadian! We have to get Canada to end this strike!
Uh, hi, we want you to end this strike. [he's calling from his house, with the other boys standing back aways]
We totally think you should have more money.
Huh? Well we don't really have that much money.
The Internet?
They said we have to give them money that we make on the Internet.
We'd have to put something up on the Internet that everyone would find fascinating.
[walks over to the window] Don't worry, Ike! The strike will be over soon! [Ike is on his back]
[finds the phone...] Excuse me. [...leaves his seat and exits the waiting room. Then he takes the call] Hello?
Wait we're working on it.
Sir, we're doing everything we can.
We don't want you to die.
We have to speed this up! [to Chocolate Rain Guy] Uh, can we collect our Internet money in front of you, please?
Okay, forget it. We'll wait our turn.
Okay, we did it.
Here. [hands Mr. Abootman the money] We made ten million theoretical dollars. It's all for you. [Mr. Abootman takes the check and looks at it]
Yeah. Everyone thinks I'm a homo now.
Dude, will you just end this thing now?! My little brother is gonna die!
[picks up the phone] Hello? Will you just give this guy something, please?!
[Mr. Abootman leans on the door, crying] He just doesn't wanna look like an idiot, so he wants everyone to think the strike was for something. Just, just give him anything!
If they give you something small, will you end the strike?
Can you act like you're giving him a lot?
Ike. Ike! [Ike wakes up] It's over.
Yeah. Here you go. [hands him a Bennigan's coupon and a gumdrop. Kyle and the others head indoors]

Yeah, but you know, I learned something today. We thought we could make money on the Internet. But, while the Internet is new and exciting for creative people, it hasn't matured as a distribution mechanism to the extent that one should trade real and immediate opportunities for income for the promise of future online revenue. It will be a few years before digital distribution of media on the Internet can be monetized to the extent that necessitates content producers to forgo their fair value in more traditional media.
You're not the teacher, fatass.
You're not an awesome teacher!
The only reason we scored high was because we took the answers out of Garrison's desk! And you know it!
Kenny's!

Do you know what those kids are going to do to you?! A little middle-class white boy telling them what to do? They are going to fucking murder you! [walks away. Stan and Kenny follow. Cartman is scared, then he starts thinking]
What?
Ih it's not working.
I've even unplugged it and plugged it back in.
I have to get online before school.
It's not working here?
Where... is... the Internet?
Hey, wait a minute. [gets off the couch and walks away to think alone] Is it possible that...
I think... I know what's wrong.
This is gonna suck.
I hate you, remember? [turns away] You wanna be partners, Jimmy?
[points to the Smithy] That guy is wearing a digital watch.

Come on, this is serious!
[opens the door and leads the others in, then spots the phone] Here! Here's the phone! [Wendy gets on the stool and tries to dial out]
What's the number to dial out?
I got through. Hello, police?

The old Pioneer Village off of Kipling.
[glances back at the two men] Sister, you don't know the half of it.

[steps forward, away from the others] I'm sorry. [holds his palms up and out, then shakes them as if to hold off something] I I'm sorry, I can't do this. [then lowers them] I'm not doing this. [walks off to his right]

[leaves his desk angrily and faces Stan] Move on?! Our friend was raped, Stan! He was raped, and we all stood there and did [takes his hands, puts them side by side, and sweeps them out away from each other] nothing!
[turns around and faces Stan] Did we?! Maybe we could have stopped them!

[turns away again] I dream about it every night. Every time I close my eyes I see us just running away, running while they ray-rape him over and over again. [clenches his fists at the thought of it, then loosens the grips and turns around] And because we did nothing... they got away.
[wipes something from his forehead] I'm... glad... that you guys can just keep living. I don't think I can. [walks out of the room. Stan watches him leave, then sighs]

Why would Spielberg and Lucas do this?!
WHY ARE THEY DOING THIIIS?!
[suddenly wakes up] NOO! [sits on the edge of his bed.] Noo. No. Awwh. [sobs softly in relief] Aw no...

[gets off the chair] Stan?
I love you too.
[points at him] Did you see it?

I know it's hard to think about, but you have to be strong. Remember how that movie made you feel.

Do what you want, don't have restraint.

Cartman?
D'ow... [they both fall over unconscious.]

What did he do?

Ju-just have a little compassion, huh? I mean, everyone's gone out and bought something stupid. It's not so bad. Whichever of you guys has never bought anything frivolous, go ahead and huck the next squirrel. [a man behind Principal Victoria moves and hucks a squirrel at Garrison]

Listen, this is all you need to know: the economy is not a supernatural all-knowing entity. The economy is just an idea, made up by people, thousands of years ago. The economy is not real. And yet, it is real. Nowadays they'll give credit cards to practically anyone who applies for them. [pulls out an envelope] I applied for this yesterday to prove a point. It is an American Express Platinum card. [from Kyle's position, one can see hundreds of people listening to him] It has no spending limit. [cries of shock rise from the crowd] Do not be afraid! This is only plastic. It's just something made up by people. Truly meaningless until we put our faith in it. Faith is what makes an economy exist. Without faith, it is only plastic cards and paper money.
I just have a feeling this might be the last time we get to do this.

[looks at Cartman for a few seconds, then enunciates] Whoever it might happen to be, I'm not giving him the opportunity. Tomorrow I'm going to do something. Something I've known I would have to do restore people's faith.
There's no choice anymore, guys. Don't worry about me. I've been preparing for this for a while now. [looks down at his plate]
It's okay, Ma.
[pays it off, with difficulty.] Heunh. [Randy smiles and walks away]
[on the sofa watching the TV] Aww, come on!
Come on guys, we gotta go! [leads the boys down the hall]
It was just thirty minutes of two women queefing on people!
Robbed us of our innocence.
Calm down Butters! The men are taking action. But we need to take your picture.
We know, Cartman!
Jimmy, exactly what part of the fishsticks joke did Cartman write?
Let me guess: you wrote the joke, and Cartman just laid on the couch eating Twizzlers.
I knew it! Don't let that fat turd walk all over you, Jimmy! Stand up for yourself!
What?
Craig, if Cartman didn't do anything, then he doesn't deserve any of the credit!
No dude, screw that! Jimmy, if Cartman didn't write the joke, then definitely don't sign any patent papers with him! Just say "Cartman, you didn't have anything to do with this joke and you know it!"
Dude, get out of here! I'm peeing.
You know what, Cartman? I believe you.

Yes, I believe that you believe you helped write that joke. That's how people like you work! Your ego is so out of whack that it will do whatever it can to protect itself. And people with a messed up ego can do these mental gymnastics to convince themselves they're awesome, when really, they're just douchebags! [turns and leaves the bathroom]
Wow, you know, Cartman? That is an awesome idea. You should totally go to Somalia.
No, I'm being totally serious. That is the best idea you've ever had. You should run away to Mogadishu. You should go there right away. I'll even help pay for your ticket.
Nono, you're right. Somalia is an oasis of treasure and waterfalls. It's totally the pirate's life.
Well, c-cause dude, I'm Jewish, a-and you know...
[puts his hands together and prays] Please. Please let him go.
Yeah? Okay, and you checked with Kenny and Tolkien? He's not just staying at their houses?
Yes! I can't help but take some credit for this. I helped convince him to go!
[chuckles] Oh for sure, dude! It's the most God-forsaken place on the planet! Things are finally gonna be normal around here.
I'll call you back. [hangs up. Sheila approaches him.]
What? Are you sure?

[takes the note and reads it aloud] "Dear Mommy and Daddy: I am running away. I am sorry, but I can no longer handle the monotony of middle-class life. Everyone at school is a fucking idiot, and if one more person talked to me about that Susan Boyle performance of Les Misrables I was going to puke my balls out through my mouth. I love you all, but I have to move on. I'm going to Somalia to be a-" to be a pirate?! Oh shit!
Oh God. What have I done?

This isn't paradise and you know it! The people here are starving and dying! The whole world has used Somalia as a dumping ground for toxic waste. Even the fish here are radioactive! [a fish walks out of the water on hind legs, squawks, turn around and goes back into the ocean] Cartman, just give me my brother [Cartman turns around and faces Kyle] and let us get out of here!
Cartman, knock it off!
They never grow old because they die before they're 30!
[comes out of his room] Ike! Ike, what?!
Guys, Ike has gotten worse. I'm really worried about him. He says he's still seeing dead celebrities.
I don't know. Last night we found him hiding in the kitchen pantry. He was screaming the name "Billy Mays" over and over again.
What?
What?! Are you serious?!
Dude, why the hell would you DO that?!
NO, why the hell would you keep eating something that made you crap blood?!
What was what?
Ya see Ike? There's nothing. There's nothing for you to be afraid of.
It's all just in your head, Ike.
I just... don't understand it.
But, dude this doesn't make any sense. I mean, if you know it's going to make you crap blood, why wouldn't you at least just try eating less of it?
But of course it matters, because you should be concerned there's blood in your underwear. [to Stan] Do you understand this?
Purgatory? What's that?
What?
Mister... Jackson, y-you aren't alive. You're in purgatory.
Mr. Jackson, please, you're causing a lot of problems.
Ike! Ike! Wake up buddy! Wake up! Ike, you've gotta wake up, please! [Ike's eyes slowly open] Eh there you go. That's good. [Ike looks around] Oh Ike. I thought I lost you, little brother.
Hey! What the hell are you doing inside my little brother?!
Come back here! [the boys give chase]
Hey! Heeey!
Dude, asshole, you're keeping a lot of other celebrities in purgatory!
What the hell are we going to do??

[still trying to make sense of Cartman's ...problem] Okay, here's the one part that really makes no sense to me: [puts both his hands on the table and spreads his fingers out] the first time you saw blood stains on your underwear, were you alarmed?
So then why do you just ignore it using something as stupid as Chipotaway?
Your mom... uses Chipotlaway... to clean blood stains... out of your underwear?
And then takes you to Chipotle, and buys you more?
What has Michael Jackson always tried to be?

Well what the hell are we gonna do? Dress him up in a princess gown and, and parade him around like the parents on those awful child pageants? [Kyle looks at his friends, then down at the floor. His friends look at each other. Yes, Kyle...]
Alright, Michael! [Kenny mumbles something]
Aww crap!
We're totally screwed! [Brandy and her mom walk by. Brandy's actually a redhead] They took the two best judges away!
Aw dude, this is hopeless!
[not making the connection] So what?!
Yeah!
Ike! [runs up to him. The other boys follow] Ike, you're back!
It's okay, Ike, you're going to be... okay.
So what?
Butters, I think you should reconsider this.
Dude, you don't want your first kiss to be something you paid for. It's supposed to be special.
Did you guys hear what's going on? There's like four girls at the school now offering to kiss boys for money.

[starts to get bored]

Why?

What is?
What is all this?

Cartman, [leaves his chair] I did some research on the Danish Web site you've been helping out. You do realize that once TrollTrace is online, anybody can use it on anyone, right?

Right, but somebody, like me, could look up your entire Internet history, print it out, and give it to Heidi. I would imagine there's some things you've done or said on the Internet you wouldn't want Heidi to know about.

[stops thinking back] Oh my God. Oh my God! Ike, come on! [grabs Ike's hand and rushes out the front door with him. Sheila hears the front door open and looks around for her boys. She reaches the open front door]

Officials have stated that all communication with Denmark has end, and that a military strike on the country is now imminent.

[Looks at phone in shock and then thinks of an answer] I understand that you're a dipshit little gay puppet.

With a dirty asshole.

[comes into view with Cartman and Stan] Jesus Christ! Where'd all these other people come from?!

What are we doing?

And there were bear prints in the snow?

ManBearPig?

Nothing. I didn't mean-

Go where?
Al Gore isn't dead.

It's Satan.
Work together how??
Credits? [some clapping is heard. The boys turn around and see Al Gore by a movie projector]
Satan!
[he and the other boys are starting to tear up] No. Satan, you can't die.

[tears streaming from his face] Dude, this is pretty fucked up right here.

Stan!
How'd you find us here?

Can we get another goalie, please?!
Go! [no reaction] GO! [thumps the Box to get Cartman's attention]
Go down the slide or get out of the way!

[Stan, Clyde, and Tolkien look on] I got news for you, Cartman! Everyone has anxiety! Everyone gets nervous! Everyone is afraid being around people! Everyone has feelings they'd rather stay home alone! And you know what they do? They get over it. And they stop being a piece of shit!
Yes!
What? No. No! What did I just do?
What do you mean?
[music picks up] Four bikes, one common theme.
[pulls out his phone and starts tapping away] I'll start looking for costumes! What theme are we thinking?

Oh yeah! The mall!
There's nobody here.
Are you the only one still at the mall?

They look amazing.
[notices Kenny arriving] All right, Kenny's here. [to Kenny] Come on, dude. We're gonna take 'em for a test spin.

How's it look like it's going? There's no way we're going to win this stupid bike parade!
[comes out to the driveway] Face it Stan! Our bikes suck! We're gonna lose! We're gonna be the laughingstock of the whole thing!
I wish there never was a bike parade.
What's offensive about a bike parade?

I can't believe Kenny bailed on us just because he thinks Jeff Bezos is a bad guy.
Such bullcrap.

[turns away from the bridge, followed by Stan and Cartman] No. No! The problem is that when it comes to outrage, your average person actually doesn't give a shit, unless it has something to do with them.
Kenny was right about you. You're a bad guy!
Why are you doing this?!
What do you want?
Yeah, 'cause you were gonna snap her bra.
Fuck you.

Hello?
Mom! Dad!
Goddamit, Cartman!
Here! [the agent is shocked and looks around, then looks at David, approaching]

Okay, let me try to put this in terms you people will understand. You know superhero movies, right?

What you're doing here is creating a Mexican Joker! [The agents get alarmed again] And what's a Mexican Joker gonna do? He's gonna grow up and have memories of being wronged by you, and he will grow and wait, and then finally [makes a fist with his right hand and pounds it into his left hand] fight back with a passion unlike anything you've ever seen!
No, it could be any of them! That's the point! You don't know which kid in there is gonna snap from being separated and locked down like this!
Mexican Joker doesn't care! When that kid grows up, all that will matter is getting back at all of you!
What the fuck are you doing here?!
I haven't seen my parents in *two weeks*! Nobody even knows where my little brother is!
Wait. I have an idea how to get everyone out of here. Get everyone's aluminum foil and some scissors.
Just do it before I kill you!
Shema Israel Adonai Eloheinu, Adonai ehad. ["Hear, Israel, the Lord is our God, the Lord is One."]
Goddamnit, nobody here is Mexican Joker! That's not what I meant! The future is not set! We make decisions now that affect our future!
NO!!
Anything happen while we were gone?
Cartman can't come to this school anymore?
Oh my God. [smiles] I don't know how long this will last, but I'm gonna savor every minute.
We're just saying, Butters, that sometimes it all seems a little codependent.
Just hike the stupid ball, Cartman.

Mississippi one Mississippi two Mississippi three Mississippi four Mississippi five Mississippi six Mississippi seven Mississippi eight Mississippi nine Mississippi ten Mississippi eleven Mississippi twelve Mississippi thirteen Mississippi fourteen Mississippi.
Dude, you're really into board games.
A bacterial infection? In her stomach?
So what can you do for her?
Ike, if Mom lives, we can't let anyone ever know about this.
Yes!
Yuch. [tosses it away, then wipes his hands clean on his jacket.]
Yeesh.
Eewww!
Aaagh! [runs off]
[wakes up and sits upright] Aaah!
Do you guys have any idea what I'm saying?! Half the cells in our bodies aren't human! Right now there are alive creatures in your eyelashes and in your teeth!
So?! Right now, that straw has a bunch of little bugs and they're going in your mouth and mixing with trillions of other little bugs that are alive inside you! You aren't even totally you!
Okay, guys, listen. My mom had a fecal transplant.
Why?
What?! Eww! No!
That is disgusting. Absolutely not!

I said "no", and that's final!

You are NOT stealing my mom's shit!

But where does it stop?! Then, are people just gonna start wanting skinny people's microbiomes to be skinny? Or an athlete's microbiome to feel athletic and young again?
Well like, what about Tom Brady's poop?
I'm just saying that Tom Brady seems to work really hard on his diet and stuff. His shit must be pretty good.
[uncomfortable from the hard stare] What?
The bookcase. [presses a button on the panel in front of him and the bookcase recedes and opens up, revealing a vault full of Tom Brady's poop in mason jars.]

I didn't know. My microbiome did. All along they were trying to tell me something. I really learned that I'm not just me. I'm also all the creatures inside of me. From now on, I'm gonna trust my gut a little more. [pats his belly]
Put it back to Mandalorian, Jimmy! Nobody likes PC Babies.
Yeah! Come on, Sophie!
Yeah, what the hell happened?
Hi.
What are you doing here??
Dude, get out of my house! If you wanna talk, we can go outside!
[covers his mouth and nose under his jacket] Dude, you could be spreading germs! [backs away]
So?

Hey dude.

[awed by this act of mercy] I don't believe it.

[the boys suddenly stop, right in front of Butters' house] You're not posting anything! Do you have any idea what you've done?

Why do people think we all did the period joke?
You guys are gonna go and tell everyone the truth about who's fault this is! I didn't do anything!
What?! Dude! [to Stan] Are you just gonna stand there and listen to this crap?!
Will you shut up about that!? Nobody cares about your stupid broship! [Kenny starts to cry and leaves, while Cartman and Kyle sadly look at him]
Yes.
[points at Cartman and Kenny] Because you guys pulled a prank and made the teacher leave, and now everybody hates us.

Cartman, just stick to the fucking plan!
RUN!!
[angry] Why did you almost blow it at the very end, you idiot?!
[walks up to Stan] Will you please say something to him?!

All good?

[irritated] What?
[angrily] What are you doing?
[points outside] We are giving these to the teachers at the school!

["[angrily] You guys are being selfish! You're not thinking about what's best for the broship. You're thinking about what's best for you. [walks up to the tray with the vaccines he picks it up] I'm gonna put these somewhere safe so no one gets tempted to do the wrong thing! "]
[looking at his phone] Oh, crap. [he taps his phone screen] Hey, dad. Look, I'm okay. I won't be home until tomorrow 'cause... well, I'm doing something really important.
[confused] You're not... worried?
[annoyed] They're for our teachers.
It's not like that.
Dad, please don't-
[closing his eyes] Please don't say it.
[lowers his phone] Shit.
[panicked] I'm just getting things ready to go.
Alright, Stan, look. It's just the pressure of everything, okay!? My dad called and... I don't want my mom to die.
[he and Stan look away] Nothing, Kenny. Everything's fine.
Butters? [points to Butters] You're a part of this too?
Oh no! Oh, Jesus, look! [a crowd of adults are running towards South Park Elementary school]
[angry] What was that!? You know we can't get into the school!
You didn't even try! [looks to Stan]. He didn't try because he wants to sell the vaccines for money!
Wow. Okay. I thought we had gotten past that, but --
Are you seriously saying what I think?
[lifts the cooler with the vaccines] We still have a bunch of vaccines here. What happens now?
Uh huh.
Do we really have to do this? That- that all seems overly confusing.
Aw, come on. What about sleepovers? We can't take those away from Kenny.
I don't even know what to say...
We set out to do something. I'm not letting our broship fall to the pandi just yet.
Mrs. Nelson? We're here!
We got your vaccination for you, Mrs. Nelson.

We didn't even do anything wrong!
Dude!
[he answers] Hey Stan.

Yeah, dude, cuz Cartman's a fuckin' moron.

Dad! Dad, there's this new place and you can actually go and shoot each other, only it's soft BBs and they're biodegradable, and the guns are, like, totally real except you don't actually get hurt, and it's like paintball except for there's no mess, and the stuff all looks totally real, and it's called Airsoft and can I get one?

There's an airsoft field where everybody plays on teams, and I promise I'll take good care of the equipment, and if you think about it, it's a really great hobby for team building and learning communication and

I was just thinking if you could come to the Airsoft store with me  [clasps his hands together] please, please, please, all my friends already bought their stuff, and it's totally a way for us to play outside like you always say  [rushes out to the door] come on, please only we can't tell mom cuz she won't understand, but it's totally safe cuz you wear eye protection.
Here it is! Isn't this cool?!
Come on, dad! You gotta check it out!
No, dad! It's Airsoft. It's like paintball, only it's way cooler and it just looks totally real.
Dad please. I'm not a baby anymore. The other guys  they already got their stuff. We're playing today! Can I please just get, like, an AK-47 and maybe a glock?
[excitedly] Yeah, yeah! It really is! [he walks away to check out other merchandise]
I got you, Cartman!
I totally got you! I heard it hit your jacket. Say hit and and go back to respawn.
Ow, oww! [he raises his hand and walks off] Hit!
That was so cool!
That was seriously the best time I've had in forever!
I know! My teenager said he's gonna come over and show me how to clean my gun! [he notices Cartman crying] Cartman? Are you ok?
I took a BB right to the face with a sniper rifle. It was so great, dad!
I'm not a baby anymore, dad! [the doorbell rings] Ooh! Oh, that's probably my teenager! See ya, dad! I love you! [he makes his way to go open the door]
[the doorbell ring is being constantly rung] I got it!
Yeah!
Yeah, that's right!
Cool, dude, so, uh, you wanna, like, clean our Airsoft guns?
WellLike, what kind of food do you want?
Okay! Okay! Okay! [he walks away from Trevor]
Dude, Kenny, the weirdest thing just happened. My teenager showed up at my house and he's acting really strange.
Yours did too?
What the hell are these things?
Yeah, I know! My teenager asked me to take him shopping for hair gel.
Just do your best, I'll be there as fast as I can! [hangs up the call] Okay, here it is. This is the health care aisle. Could you go a little faster?
Okay, here's all the hair product stuff. Which one would you like to use?
What?
Ugh, nothing, I'm I'm just shopping with my teenager.
Okay, but you asked me if I could buy you some hair gel.
Your guy wants hair gel, too?
I just wanna get to the Airsoft field. Stan says your team is killing them.
Yeah, we'll see when I use my sniper rifle!
Well, you're lucky. At least your teenager doesn't threaten to kill you.
And we love it.
Well, apparently a lot of people are in the same situation we're in.
I've been reading this book"Help, My Teenager Hates Me".
Yeahand it has some interesting ideas. It says we're basically just dealing with an age difference and we need to try and connect with them.
It sayswe should take them camping.
Yeah, check 'em out!
There's a lake over there where we can rent kayaks!
No I don't think I'm gonna go
You wouldn't understand, Dad. I just can't deal with teenagers.
You know, I just [Kyle starts to get teary eyed]I just wanted to have funand shoot my friends. [Kyle reaches closer to Gerald, crying] I-I just wanted to shoot my friends, dad.
We did! They said they hate the teenagers just as much as anybody, but they can't get rid of them. And we've got no one else to partner with.
We got new partners, guys!
[to the parents] Hey, thanks, you guys. We couldn't have gotten rid of the teenagers without you.
Come on, guys!

Episode Title: Credigree Weed St. Patrick's Day Special
Lines: Hey, Butters.
Hey, dudes.
Just wondering if you guys have seen me and Tolkien's latest TikTok?
Well, anyway you guys gotta check it out when you get a chance. See ya later!
Hey, Stan.
Oh, no sorry. I was actually just seeing if you had a phone charger I could borrow. Me and Tolkien are making another TikTok video and my stupid phone died!
Thanks, dude! [walks away] Tolkien, I got one, dude!
Wow, that's so cool, Tolkien! Look how many likes we're getting for this one.
Yeah, what's up?
What?
[angrily] I'm not even going to justify that with a response. Because repeating a derogatory slur, even for the purpose of refuting it, can make stupid people think it's valid! [he storms off]
Lots of people run Hollywood!!
Hey, I didn't see you at the playground. Thought we were doing that morning TikTok.
Everything okay?

Anything like what?

[louder] Everyone! I do not run Hollywood! Get a fucking clue!

[Cartman creeps up from the bushes.] Oh my God, are you listening to yourself? You of all people should have some compassion!
[Cartman smiles at the fight from behind the bushes.] You seriously dont know why? You know that Jews have stood alongside Blacks since the Civil Rights movement began, right?
Im just saying I thought youd be a better friend. Cause youre like

You people?! No, it works that way for you people!
[Kyle takes the tripod and prepares to leave.] I dont wanna make TikToks with you anymore!
Good!
W-What do you mean?
Tolkien?
Holy shit!

My message is, we can't control what people say, so we have to be smart about what we choose to believe. If one idiot says that a certain group "runs Hollywood", look into it. With very minimal effort, you will find that "Hollywood" is a multi-tiered industry run by tens of thousands of people from all over the world. In the past, Jews were shut out of most professions, so they came to dominate vaudeville, which back then was considered too low-brow for good Christians. Those Jews eventually moved West and started the first movie studios when movies were also considered work for the underclass, and their descendents are now a decent percentage of the thousands of people of all races that make Hollywood run.
Woah, woah-- wait, what? Woah.

Ike -- Ike, come on, dude, you can't keep doing this.
Ike, the Queen died like four months ago. You gotta let it go.
Okay, it's 7:00, it's my turn to use the computer.
Ike, me and my friends are playing "Darktide" right now. Get off!

What stinks?
[confused] My brand?
I'm just -- I-I'm just me.
Butters, this seems very out of character for you.
Brand management?

What the hell?

You guys, I am so sorry. I totally was going to play with you guys online but the Prince of Canada and his wife moved in across the street from me. They have this huge jet parked in front of my house and then they kept trying to get me to buy their stupid book and -- and, anyway, I'm sorry I messed up another game night.
Well, I just want you guys to know that I am a reliable, fun-loving, punctual victim.
I'm really working on myself! You're gonna like what you see! [His smile drops]
God, fuck these people!
Yeah, the neighbors across the steet are setting off fireworks and it's 10:30 at night!

Yes. They're being super loud, and I'm trying to work on my brand! [he checks his window] Oh, god damn it. Now, the Prince is playing polo on the lawn![The Prince is shown playing polo, continuing to be very loud along with his wife.]
Hey, can you two fucking keep it down?!
Yeah, nobody gives a shit! Will you two just shut up, and go away?! [Another ball hits Kyle's window, smashing it.]

It seriously is driving me crazy! The prince plays drums all day. I don't think he even has a job. And I don't know what the hell she does. Why they even left Canada is beyond me. And, like, she seems to just boss him around, and make him do whatever she wants. I mean, why did they even leave Canada and move to South Park, anyway?
Say what?
I don't care about them either!
[He stutters and isn't able to come up with anything]
I'm sick of hearing about them! But I can't get away from them! They're everywhere! In my fucking face!
Fine, I won't talk about them anymore.
Ok, just one last thing -- did you know the Prince sleeps-

But I just don't feel like my brand is who I really am on the inside.
I guess so.
I want them to think I'm not gonna complain about things. I'm more thick-skinned.
And I want people to think I'm stronger, mentally, than I probably already am.
I just don't know if I can--
I don't care. Don't care. [he goes inside]
Hey, guys! How you doin?!
I'm great! Got some good sleep last night. Just letting things roll right off my back, you know? 'Cause that's the kind of guy I am.
Hey, you guys want to play "Darktide" after school? Or if not, whatever. I'm cool either way.
Cool, whatever. I'm care-free and unflappable. I'll catch you guys at lunch! [he walks away, Jimmy approaches him]

Hey! Whoa, whoa, whoa. What the hell is going on?!
Butters, what are you doing?! This isn't you.
Okay, that does it -- come on, Butters. You're going back to CumHammer.
Come on, Butters. Hello?
Uh, no. This is an emergency. We need to talk to --

I'm not obsessed with you! It's this stupid place! Don't you see, Butters? Teaching people to think of their brand just makes people more like them. This whole thing is wrong. They're telling you guys to reduce yourselves into products instead of people to be truly understood and loved. Don't you guys want people to like you for you instead of who they want you to be? Look, we all have our faults. God knows I do. But if we just try to present and control an image of us for people to see, then, we're just performers instead of human beings.

Ike, I need to use the -- Oh no, not again...
Ike, I have to get on the computer. The Queen's been dead a long time. [Ike continues to cry] Ike! I have to get on with my friends! If I don't, they're gonna think I'm...
It's okay. Things get to you. It's who you are.
Oh. Hey, guys.
Really?
Yeah. Yeah, I have. [he smiles a bit] Thanks, guys. I'd love to play.
Dude, did you hear what happened to your girlfriend?
Dude, she got caught cheating on her essay.
You wouldn't last four hours on a job, fatass.
